An Al2O3 layer was deposited on the textured Si by magnetron sputtering and then annealed in a forming gas of hydrogen and nitrogen (H2:N2 = 10%:90% in volume) at 350 °C for 20 min to passivate the front surface of the Si substrate. Au was then deposited on Al2O3 at a rate of 5 nm/min by pulsed laser deposition with a frequency-doubled Q-switched Nd:YAG laser at a base pressure lower than 2×10-4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
